British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson, has been released from intensive care where he spent three nights receiving treatment for Coronavirus. According to the Sun UK, a spokesman said in a statement that Boris was released from intensive care on Thursday, but will remain in hospital. He said “The Prime Minister has been moved this evening from intensive care back to the ward, where he will receive close monitoring during the early phase of his recovery. “He is in extremely good spirits.” Recall that the Prime minister was admitted to a hospital on Sunday for coronavirus. He was admitted following the advice of his doctor as he continued to show persistent symptoms of Coronavirus after ten days.